verses.text_plain: And it came to pass in the eleventh year, in the third month, in the first day of the month, that the word of the Lord came unto me, saying,
verses.verse_html: 1And it came to pass in the eleventh year, in the third month, in the first day of the month, that the word of the Lord came unto me, saying,

tokens.text: And it came to pass in the eleventh

verses.text_plain: Son of man, speak unto Pharaoh king of Egypt, and to his multitude; Whom art thou like in thy greatness?
verses.verse_html: 2Son of man, speak unto Pharaoh king of Egypt, and to his multitude; Whom art thou like in thy greatness?

verses.text_plain: Behold, the Assyrian was a cedar in Lebanon with fair branches, and with a shadowing shroud, and of an high stature; and his top was among the thick boughs.
verses.verse_html:
3Behold, the Assyrian was a cedar in Lebanon with fair branches, and with a shadowing shroud, and of an high stature; and his top was among the thick boughs. ▼
▼ with fair branches: Heb. fair of branches

footnotes.body_text: ▼ with fair branches: Heb. fair of branches
footnotes.body_html: ▼ with fair branches: Heb. fair of branches

verses.text_plain: The waters made him great, the deep set him up on high with her rivers running round about his plants, and sent out her little rivers unto all the trees of the field.
verses.verse_html:
4The waters made him great, the deep set him up on high with her rivers running round about his plants, and sent out her little rivers unto all the trees of the field. ▼
▼ made…: or, nourished him
 , ▼
▼ set…: or, brought him up
 , ▼

footnotes.body_html: ▼ made…: or, nourished him

verses.text_plain: Therefore his height was exalted above all the trees of the field, and his boughs were multiplied, and his branches became long because of the multitude of waters, when he shot forth.
verses.verse_html:
5Therefore his height was exalted above all the trees of the field, and his boughs were multiplied, and his branches became long because of the multitude of waters, when he shot forth. ▼
▼ when…: or, when it sent them forth

footnotes.body_text: ▼ when…: or, when it sent them forth
footnotes.body_html: ▼ when…: or, when it sent them forth

verses.text_plain: All the fowls of heaven made their nests in his boughs, and under his branches did all the beasts of the field bring forth their young, and under his shadow dwelt all great nations.
verses.verse_html: 6All the fowls of heaven made their nests in his boughs, and under his branches did all the beasts of the field bring forth their young, and under his shadow dwelt all great nations.

verses.text_plain: Thus was he fair in his greatness, in the length of his branches: for his root was by great waters.
verses.verse_html: 7Thus was he fair in his greatness, in the length of his branches: for his root was by great waters.

verses.text_plain: The cedars in the garden of God could not hide him: the fir trees were not like his boughs, and the chesnut trees were not like his branches; nor any tree in the garden of God was like unto him in his beauty.
verses.verse_html: 8The cedars in the garden of God could not hide him: the fir trees were not like his boughs, and the chesnut trees were not like his branches; nor any tree in the garden of God was like unto him in his beauty.

verses.text_plain: I have made him fair by the multitude of his branches: so that all the trees of Eden, that were in the garden of God, envied him.
verses.verse_html: 9I have made him fair by the multitude of his branches: so that all the trees of Eden, that were in the garden of God, envied him.

verses.text_plain: Therefore thus saith the Lord God; Because thou hast lifted up thyself in height, and he hath shot up his top among the thick boughs, and his heart is lifted up in his height;
verses.verse_html: 10Therefore thus saith the Lord God; Because thou hast lifted up thyself in height, and he hath shot up his top among the thick boughs, and his heart is lifted up in his height;

verses.text_plain: I have therefore delivered him into the hand of the mighty one of the heathen; he shall surely deal with him: I have driven him out for his wickedness.
verses.verse_html:
11I have therefore delivered him into the hand of the mighty one of the heathen; he shall surely deal with him: I have driven him out for his wickedness. ▼
▼ he…: Heb. in doing he shall do unto him

tokens.text: with him: I have driven him out

footnotes.body_text: ▼ he…: Heb. in doing he shall do unto him
footnotes.body_html: ▼ he…: Heb. in doing he shall do unto him

verses.text_plain: And strangers, the terrible of the nations, have cut him off, and have left him: upon the mountains and in all the valleys his branches are fallen, and his boughs are broken by all the rivers of the land; and all the people of the earth are gone down from his shadow, and have left him.
verses.verse_html: 12And strangers, the terrible of the nations, have cut him off, and have left him: upon the mountains and in all the valleys his branches are fallen, and his boughs are broken by all the rivers of the land; and all the people of the earth are gone down from his shadow, and have left him.

verses.text_plain: Upon his ruin shall all the fowls of the heaven remain, and all the beasts of the field shall be upon his branches:
verses.verse_html: 13Upon his ruin shall all the fowls of the heaven remain, and all the beasts of the field shall be upon his branches:

verses.text_plain: To the end that none of all the trees by the waters exalt themselves for their height, neither shoot up their top among the thick boughs, neither their trees stand up in their height, all that drink water: for they are all delivered unto death, to the nether parts of the earth, in the midst of the children of men, with them that go down to the pit.
verses.verse_html:
14To the end that none of all the trees by the waters exalt themselves for their height, neither shoot up their top among the thick boughs, neither their trees stand up in their height, all that drink water: for they are all delivered unto death, to the nether parts of the earth, in the midst of the children of men, with them that go down to the pit. ▼
▼ their trees…: or, stand upon themselves for their height

verses.text_plain: Thus saith the Lord God; In the day when he went down to the grave I caused a mourning: I covered the deep for him, and I restrained the floods thereof, and the great waters were stayed: and I caused Lebanon to mourn for him, and all the trees of the field fainted for him.
verses.verse_html:
15Thus saith the Lord God; In the day when he went down to the grave I caused a mourning: I covered the deep for him, and I restrained the floods thereof, and the great waters were stayed: and I caused Lebanon to mourn for him, and all the trees of the field fainted for him. ▼
▼ to mourn: Heb. to be black

tokens.text: for him, and all the trees

footnotes.body_text: ▼ to mourn: Heb. to be black
footnotes.body_html: ▼ to mourn: Heb. to be black

verses.text_plain: I made the nations to shake at the sound of his fall, when I cast him down to hell with them that descend into the pit: and all the trees of Eden, the choice and best of Lebanon, all that drink water, shall be comforted in the nether parts of the earth.
verses.verse_html: 16I made the nations to shake at the sound of his fall, when I cast him down to hell with them that descend into the pit: and all the trees of Eden, the choice and best of Lebanon, all that drink water, shall be comforted in the nether parts of the earth.

verses.text_plain: They also went down into hell with him unto them that be slain with the sword; and they that were his arm, that dwelt under his shadow in the midst of the heathen.
verses.verse_html: 17They also went down into hell with him unto them that be slain with the sword; and they that were his arm, that dwelt under his shadow in the midst of the heathen.

verses.text_plain: To whom art thou thus like in glory and in greatness among the trees of Eden? yet shalt thou be brought down with the trees of Eden unto the nether parts of the earth: thou shalt lie in the midst of the uncircumcised with them that be slain by the sword. This is Pharaoh and all his multitude, saith the Lord God.
verses.verse_html: 18To whom art thou thus like in glory and in greatness among the trees of Eden? yet shalt thou be brought down with the trees of Eden unto the nether parts of the earth: thou shalt lie in the midst of the uncircumcised with them that be slain by the sword. This is Pharaoh and all his multitude, saith the Lord God.
